is a 1995 video game for the Super Famicom that was released to an exclusively Japanese market.
This video game combines the futuristic elements of F-Zero with the whimsical elements of Super Mario Kart. Players can select from various tracks and confront numerous dead ends and alternate turns. There are six drivers in a race. The four main characters of the game are: Ultraman Powered (from the Ultra Series), Kamen Rider ZO (from the Kamen Rider franchise), V2 Gundam (from the Gundam franchise) and Banpresto original character Fighter Roar.
